failed to live up to many past marketopening agreements it is 
critical in this first round of talks to review the initiative 
that our negotiators emphasize that the united states expects japan 
to fully implement all commitments made he said 
baucus who chairs a senate trade subcommittee said that where 
compliance was lacking the administration must be prepared to use 
sections of us law that permit economic retaliation if barriers 
are erected to prevent sales of american products 
among the commitments made by japan in june were to increase 
public works spending reduce the time it takes to issue patents 
and begin vigorous criminal enforcement against bidrigging 
pricefixing and other anticompetitive business practices 
while past negotiations with the japanese have sought access for 
specific american industries the new talks sought to address 
fundamental problems in the american and japanese economies that 
have contributed to the trade imbalance 
