washington state has an estimated 30 million old tires which 
pose a major fire and environmental hazard that grows by 4 million 
to 5 million tires a year officials say but so far the state has 
been cool to the kings idea 
the king wants the state to spend 255 million up front to 
gather chip and ship the 30 million tires to his kingdom a group 
of islands about 3000 miles southwest of honolulu he also wants a 
guaranteed supply of old tires 
by taking the tires off the states hands the deal would lay 
a sound base for future trade and commercial development projects 
with tonga the king told gov booth gardner in a recent letter 
