a group of archaeologists is searching 
a wooded area minutes from downtown for evidence that spanish 
explorer hernando desoto visited chattanooga 450 years ago 
every weekend members of the chattanooga regional 
anthropological association head across the tennessee river from 
downtown and sift through the soil at moccasin bend for spanish 
artifacts 
theyre looking for proof that desoto visited indians there in 
1540 while searching for gold silver and jewels in a threeyear 
expedition across the southeastern united states 
historians know that the explorer ventured into tennessee and 
that spaniards made contact with local indians but they are not 
sure whether the two events coincided 
he either came through the sphere of influence of chattanooga 
just to the east or he marched into it and made contact and perhaps 
stayed as long as a month in its towns dealing with its chieftains 
and extorting corn and other provisions for the army said major 
