a senate committee on tuesday cleared the way 
for a national park service study on the feasibility of making 
permanent a pedestrian bridge to ellis island and the statue of 
liberty 
the senate appropriations committee approved the study proposal 
from sen frank lautenberg dnj as part of the 1991 interior 
appropriations bill 
