approval by the full senate 
the foot bridge which connects liberty state park in new jersey 
with ellis island has been used by construction workers 
rehabilitating the immigration center it was slated to be phased 
out in 1992 however new jersey lawmakers upset at the 6 
perperson cost of getting to the monuments by ferry have suggested 
the bridge be retained 
