socialists called the funeral an example of excessive 
security 
little of that kind of police presence is visible in tokyo yet 
although some checkpoints have been set up on major streets 
emperor akihito assumed the throne immediately after his father 
died in january 1989 but the formal enthronement had to be delayed 
for a yearlong mourning period 
