net withdrawals from the nations savings and 
loans slowed to 7 billion in may after soaring to a record 151 
billion a month earlier the government said tuesday 
depositors withdrew 32 billion from 2471 solvent sampls and 
another 38 billion from the 312 failed institutions operated 
under government control the office of thrift supervision said 
that compares with a net outflow in april of 96 billion at 
solvent institutions and 54 billion at governmentrun thrifts 
for the first five months of the year withdrawals totaled 464 
billion compared with 356 billion during the same period a year 
ago 
