ecosystem said sally shoup of greenpeace we have to stop this 
devastation of the other creatures on the planet if we want to 
protect ourselves 
i think whales are special she said i think they are 
intelligent creatures i think icelanders can understand that as 
well 
the savethewhales campaign began in 1972 when the landmark 
un conference on the environment in a 530 vote passed a 
resolution calling for a 10year moratorium on whaling whalers 
killed 46000 whales that year 
the united states immediately proposed the moratorium to the 
whaling commission which rejected it but the us continued to 
push in 1982 the commission finally approved a moratorium 
beginning in 1986 
what we were going to do was take five years of no whaling 
said evans the us representative to the commission well we 
havent had five years of no whaling because iceland invented 
scientific whaling 
a clause in the international whaling convention allows the 
killing of whales for scientific purposes iceland exploited it 
you have the same boats and the same people and you take the 
same whales and you sell it to the same people and you call it 
scientific whaling said roger payne a noted whale expert and 
president of the long term research institute in lincoln mass 
its a joke 
johann sigurjonsson senior whale specialist at icelands marine 
research institute vigorously disagreed those who have been 
following what were doing understand the seriousness of what were 
doing he said 
in 1985 the last year of its commercial whaling operation 
iceland killed 344 whales it caught 116 in 1986 and the number 
declined to 68 in 1989 this year iceland shut down its whaling 
operation entirely but it continues to press vigorously for a 
resumption of commercial killing of fin sei and minke whales 
congress has passed several laws that allow the united states to 
impose economic sanctions against countries that violate whaling 
commission regulations 
icelands critics have argued that the scientific whaling is 
merely commercial whaling under another name and have pressed the 
united states to impose sanctions the united states might be 
reluctant to do so however because iceland is the site of a 
strategic nato base 
payne said the methods used to estimate whale populations are 
highly imprecise and that the icelandic scientific research has 
shown us nothing we didnt know before 
it could take as long as 100 years to know how many whales can 
be captured without reducing the size of a given whale population 
he said 
the international whaling commission has stopped releasing 
estimates 
