im delighted to accept it and im still in a state of 
shock miller said this morning 
miller was one of three us economists to win the 1990 nobel 
prize in economics he will share the 700000 prize with harry 
markowitz of the city university of new york and william sharpe of 
stanford university 
markowitz 63 a chicago native cited for developing the theory 
of portfolio choice said he gave up any hopes of winning the nobel 
prize nine years ago when yale university professor james tobin was 
honored for work on another facet of portfolio theory 
id thought it was never going to happen markowitz said 
after news that he had won the 1990 prize reached him in tokyo 
where he starts teaching a class at tokyo university on wednesday 
there was a prize given to james tobin also in portfolio 
theory but applied more to economics and less to business 
administration than mine 
i figured thats it theyve given the prize for portfolio 
theory 
markowitzs portfolio theory analyzes how wealth can be best 
invested in assets that differ in their expected return and risk 
the theory involves use of computers and data bases and is used by 
large institutional investors in the united states markowitz said 
miller of the university of chicagos graduate school of 
business was honored for his fundamental contributions to the 
theory of corporate finance 
the swedish academy of sciences said the 67yearold miller made 
the most important achievements in the theory of corporate finance 
and the evaluation of firms on markets 
in a telephone interview the boston native said he got the news 
in an earlymorning phone call and thought it was a crank call at 
first when he didnt hear anything on the line 
but he said his heart kind of stopped a bit when he heard 
the news from the accented voice on the other end of the phone 
he worked initially in collaboration with 1985 economics 
prizewinner franco modigliani of the united states 
the corporatefinance theory explains the relation or lack of 
one among firms capital asset structure and dividend policy on 
the one hand and their market value on the other 
our work was always known as the modiglianimiller 
propositions of corporate finance miller said he then won it 
for his contributions with me but also for his other work in 
economics 
theyve already recognized the work once and now im getting 
the other half 
sharpe 56 a native of cambridge mass won for his 
contributions to the theory of price formation for financial 
assets the socalled capital asset pricing model the academy 
said 
